# Code Review Checklist

## Automatic Rejection

- ANY hard-coded API keys, credentials, tokens, secrets
- ANY `as any` type assertions
- ANY hard-coded hex colors in components (use CSS variables or theme)
- Variables prefixed with `_` that are actually used
- Console.log statements left in production code

## Security & Data

- [ ] No hard-coded API keys, tokens, or sensitive data
- [ ] Environment variables used for configuration
- [ ] No `as any` or `as unknown as <Type>` assertions
- [ ] User input is properly validated and sanitized

## Design System

- [ ] All colors use CSS variables or theme values
- [ ] Consistent spacing using design system tokens
- [ ] Responsive design with proper breakpoints
- [ ] Accessible color contrast ratios

## React Patterns

- [ ] All API calls use TanStack Query hooks
- [ ] Query keys include ALL parameters affecting result
- [ ] No unnecessary try-catch (TanStack Query handles errors)
- [ ] Conditional queries use `skipToken` or conditional rendering
- [ ] Components follow single responsibility principle

## Accessibility

- [ ] All images have alt text
- [ ] Form inputs have associated labels
- [ ] Interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- [ ] ARIA attributes used correctly where needed
- [ ] Color is not the only means of conveying information

## Variable Naming

- [ ] `_` prefix variables must be unused - remove underscore if used
- [ ] Descriptive variable and function names
- [ ] Consistent naming conventions (camelCase for variables, PascalCase for components)

## Common Mistakes

- Hard-coded colors in style props → Use CSS variables
- Inline functions in render → Extract to useCallback or define outside
- Missing key prop in lists → Add unique key
- Unnecessary try/catch around API calls
